1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. d3 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. a3
O-O 9. Nc3 Na5 10. Ba2 Be6 11. d4 Bxa2 12. Rxa2 Nc6 13. d5 Nb8 14. Qe2 Nbd7 15.
Rd1 Qc8 16. Nh4 {Forcing the next move} g6 17. g3 Ne8 18. Ng2 Ng7 {Preparing a
possible ...f5. I would love to have a pawn on b7. Because on b5 is a bit of a
weakness in this situations.} 19. Bh6 Nf6 {Intending a possible ...Ng4} 20. Ne3
(20. f3 Qh3 21. Be3 {And black could try ...Nd7 & ...f5}) 20... Qh3 21. Bxg7
Kxg7 22. b4 h5 23. a4 (23. Rb1) 23... a5 $1 24. Rb1 axb4 25. Rxb4 bxa4 26.
Raxa4 {Black manages to exchange his weaknesses on the queenside.} Ng4 27. Nf1
(27. Nxg4 hxg4 28. Qf1 Qh6) 27... h4 28. f3 hxg3 29. hxg3 (29. fxg4 gxh2+ {
With the idea ...Qxc3}) 29... Nf6 {Now we have that situation of attacking
with equal material!} 30. Qg2 Qh6 31. Qh2 Qg5 32. Qd2 Qh5 33. g4 Qh8 $3 {Now
the dark squares are decisivedly weakened} 34. Nb5 Nh7 35. Qh2 (35. Nxc7 Ng5)
35... Rfb8 36. c4 (36. Rxa8 Rxa8 37. Nxc7 Ra1 (37... Ra7 38. Nb5 Ra1) 38. Rb7
Qd8 $5) 36... Qd8 {With a great position!} 37. Ne3 Bg5 38. Qe2 Bf4 39. Ng2 Bg3
40. Qe3 Ng5 41. Kf1 Qh8 (41... Qh8 42. Qxg5 Qh1+) 0-1


