1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. Be2 g6 $1 (4... Nxe4 5. Qa4+) (4... Nc6) (4...
Nbd7) (4... Bd7) 5. O-O Bg7 6. Bb5+ Nc6 {Is also an excellente move} ({In case
} 6... Bd7 7. Bxd7+ Qxd7 8. Re1 {It looks like white has lost a tempo. But
once you get these structures with white goes d4, black takes and then ...d5.
Then the bishop is misplaced on g7. It also weakens his kingside which also
makes the h-pawn advance a lot stronger. So there is some point to it.}) ({
Black has also other ways to play like...} 6... Nfd7 7. d4 O-O {Then ...Nc6
later on trying to play some Benoni-like structure. Just also not bad for
black. I won a rapid game against Fressinet.}) 7. d4 Qb6 8. Ba4 cxd4 9. cxd4
O-O 10. d5 (10. Nc3 Bg4 $1) 10... Nb8 (10... Na5 {Also good for black}) 11. Nc3
Bg4 $1 (11... Bd7 12. Bc2 {The white bishop is misplaced on a4} Bg4) 12. h3
Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Nbd7 {It looks armonious for black.} 14. Rb1 Rfc8 15. Bc2 {So I
decided to go for a kingside attack} Ne5 16. Qe2 Nfd7 17. Bg5 {So I'm asking
questions} h6 (17... Bf6 {Is fine}) 18. Bh4 (18. Bxe7 f6) 18... g5 19. Bg3 Qa6
(19... Ng6 {It was the obvious move} 20. Nd1 (20. Kh1 $5) 20... Nf4 21. Bxf4
gxf4) 20. Qd1 Rc4 (20... Nc4 21. Bd3 Nc5 22. Be2 Bxc3 23. bxc3 Nxe4 24. Qd4 {
I was not to convinced}) 21. Kh1 (21. f4 Rd4 22. Qxd4 (22. Qe1 Nd3) 22... Nf3+)
21... Rac8 (21... Ng6 22. Bd3) 22. f4 gxf4 23. Bxf4 Qb6 24. Qh5 Nf6 25. Qf5 Qd8
{With the idea ...Qd7} 26. Bb3 Rd4 27. Bxe5 dxe5 28. Rbd1 {Challenging the
rook on d4} Qd7 29. Qf3 {Ready to take on d4} Rb4 {With the idea a5-a4} 30. Rd2
Rf8 {Preparing ...Ne8-d7} (30... a5 31. Bd1) 31. g4 $1 a5 32. Rg2 Nh7 (32... a4
33. Bd1 a3 34. bxa3) 33. h4 Rb6 34. g5 Kh8 (34... Rg6 35. Rfg1 hxg5 36. hxg5)
35. Rfg1 f5 {Trying to muddy the waters} 36. Qh3 Rb4 37. gxh6 Bxh6 38. Qg3 Nf6
39. Qg6 Ng4 40. Rxg4 (40. Rxg4 Rb6 41. Qxb6 $18 (41. d6 Rxd6)) 1-0


